{"body": "This is just another example of Rails re-implementing Ruby with weird syntax. It\u2019s depressing.\n\nSpecifically, two problems:\n\n1. It duplicates existing functionality, and not only does it not provide anything extra, it's considerably less flexible than simply instantiating an object and passing in dependencies (as shown in others' examples).\n\n2. It means that new users have to learn \"the Rails way\" and \"the Ruby way\", learn the differences, and learn which situations are appropriate for each.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8390257", "created_at": "2012-09-08T16:24:10Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7520#issuecomment-8390257", "updated_at": "2012-09-08T16:24:10Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7520, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/srbaker", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3c8c4b69930a102c3ca698cc4cbcbf0b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F79fde5402cbc75ae0615c9ae4c335b46.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3c8c4b69930a102c3ca698cc4cbcbf0b", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "srbaker", "type": "User", "id": 4538, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fac1bd3543c15100b6b3"}, "id": 8390257, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7520"}
